  "summary": "Workload is lineitem-dominated (60M rows, accessed by all 5 queries); Q1 and Q6 are pure lineitem scans benefiting most from AVX512 vectorized columnar execution and zone map pruning. Q3, Q9, and Q18 involve multi-way hash joins where aggressive filter pushdown (BUILDING segment, date range, LIKE '%green%') is the primary optimization lever to reduce probe-side sizes. Q9 is the most complex (6-way join with subquery nesting) and Q18 carries the highest subquery decorrelation overhead; both require careful join ordering starting from the most selective dimension."
